
// This Hyperlambda code uses the [sockets.signal] slot to send a message to a session specified in the [.arguments] node. The [args] node contains the message details, where [message] is dynamically constructed using [strings.concat], and [type] is set to "system". This allows for sending system-type messages to the specified session.
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
